So as i understand it the &#x27;use case&#x27; is for coercing 3rd party types into your own type hierarchy. Suppose you had:<p><pre><code>  trait Foo {
    def bar(): Int
  }
</code></pre>
and 3rd party library had<p><pre><code>  final class FooBar extends java.lang.Object {
    public int bar() { /** **/ }
  }
</code></pre>
you could simply define your methods to take in a:<p><pre><code>  type BarAble = { def bar():Int }

</code></pre>
But obviously if the library class is not final, you can simply do:<p><pre><code>  type ThirdPartyFoo = FooBar with Foo
  ThirdPartyFoo <: Foo</code></pre>
